headline: Lamb Weston stock fried over Q2 miss, guidance cut, new CEO
summary: Lamb Weston (LW) is out of the frying pan and into the deep frier as shares of the frozen food company tank by over 20% in Thursday's session. The french fry maker missed fiscal second quarter earnings estimates while it cut its full-year 2025 guidance and replaced CEO Thomas Werner with its COO Michael Smith. Market Domination's Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton report on the latest developments surrounding Lamb Weston. Post Holdings (POST) was recently exploring a potential deal with Lamb Weston, before ultimately acquiring Potato Products of Idaho. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: Why Lamb Weston Stock Was Diving Today

Lamb Weston's revenue in the quarter fell by 8% year over year to $1.6 billion, which missed the consensus estimate of $1.67 billion.  The underperformance came as demand for its frozen potato products continues to be weak.

headline: Frozen French fry maker Lamb Weston names new CEO, moves to loss in Q2 and cuts outlook
summary: Lamb Weston is naming a new CEO as the frozen french fry maker moved to a loss in its second quarter and trimmed its fiscal 2025 forecast.  The Eagle, Idaho-based company said that Michael Smith, who currently serves as its chief operating officer, will become its CEO and join its board on Jan. 3, 2025.  Smith takes over the CEO post from Thomas Werner, who will serve as an adviser through Aug. 31, 2025 to help with the transition process.

headline: Lamb Weston replaces CEO amid push from Jana as forecast cuts singe shares
summary: Lamb Weston trimmed its annual forecasts and replaced its CEO with insider Michael Smith on Thursday, following pressure from activist investor Jana Partners to revamp its top management or sell itself.  Jana Partners called the decision to swap the CEO for an insider "complicit in its widespread operational and strategic debacles is just the latest stick in the eye."  The company did not immediately respond to a request for comment on Jana Partners' statement.

headline: Lamb Weston Announces Appointment of Michael J. Smith as President and Chief Executive Officer
summary: EAGLE, Idaho, December 19, 2024--Lamb Weston Holdings, Inc. (NYSE: LW) announced today the appointment of Michael J. Smith, current Chief Operating Officer of Lamb Weston, as President and Chief Executive Officer and as a member of the company’s Board of Directors, effective January 3, 2025. Mr. Smith succeeds Thomas P. Werner, who is stepping down as CEO and as a member of the Board. Mr. Werner will serve in an advisory role through August 31, 2025 to ensure a smooth transition.

headline: Nike Q2 earnings, mortgage rates update: What to Watch
summary: Market domination hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton detail the top market events investors should be watching for Thursday, December 19. Several major companies are set to report quarterly earnings across the retail and services sectors, including Accenture (ACN), Nike (NKE), FedEx (FDX), Darden Restaurants (DRI), ConAgra Brands (CAG), and Lamb Weston (LW). The health of the housing market will also be in focus as investors await fresh existing home sales data and the weekly mortgage rates report.
